Louis Hernandez Jr.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 3:52 PM ET
Technology Hardware, Storage and Peripherals

Company Overview of Avid Technology, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Louis   Hernandez Jr.Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, Avid Technology, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships50$3,652,904As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Louis Hernandez, Jr., has been the Chief Executive Officer at Avid Technology, Inc. since February 2013 and its Chairman since October 2013. Mr. Hernandez is leading Avid Technology into its next phase of growth and market leadership. He serves as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Blue Order Solutions AG. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Corporate Financial Solutions, a subsidiary of Open Solutions, LLC. He served as President ... at Avid Technology, Inc. since February 2013 until December 2016. He served as the Chairman of Open Solutions Inc. since March 2000 and also served as its Chief Executive Officer since November 1999. He served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of Open Solutions FDSI, Inc. (Alternative Name: Financial Data Solutions, Inc). He is a proven growth-oriented technology executive with expertise in operational execution and results-driven performance in a variety of complex technical fields including content management, e-commerce, workflow management and financial services. His focus and passion is to advance technology initiatives that specifically enable the active collaboration and connection between individuals, teams and businesses. From January 1998 to November 1999, he served as an Executive Vice President of RoweCom Inc. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of RoweCom from February 1997 to November 1999. Prior to RoweCom, he served as the Chief Financial Officer and Corporate Secretary for US Medical Instruments Inc. From 1990 to 1996, he worked in the business and advisory services group of Price Waterhouse LLP. He serves as the Chairman of Financial Data Solutions Inc. He serves as the Chairman of the Technology Transfer Advisory board set up by the Governor's Council to develop strategies for technology transfer and commercialization in the state. He served as the Chairman of the Connecticut Technology Council and as Vice Chairman of the Commission for Educational Technology. He served as the Vice Chairman of the Governor''s Council on Economic Competitiveness and Technology at Connecticut. Mr. Hernandez serves as a Director of ScoreBig, Inc. and Payveris, LLC. He has been a Director of HSBC Financial Corporation Limited since April 2007, Avid Technology, Inc. since February 2008, Edison International since August 25, 2016 and Southern California Edison Company since August 25, 2016. He served as a Director of Aspect Software, Inc., Aspect Software Group Holdings Ltd. from April 30, 2013 to September 29, 2015 and also Director of Aspect Software Parent, Inc. from April 2013 to September 29, 2015. He served as a Lead Director at Avid Technology, Inc. from December 2011 to February 11, 2013. He served as a Director of Open Solutions Inc. and Corporate Financial Solutions. He served as a Director of HSBC USA Inc. since May 2008 to June 30, 2013. He served as a Director of Unica Corporation since May 12, 2009. He served as a Director of HSBC Finance Corporation from May 29, 2007 to May 2008. He served as a Director of Open Solutions FDSI, Inc. He served as a Director of Edu.com, Inc. and HSBC North America Holdings Inc. He served as a Director of Mobius Management Systems, Inc. since May 6, 2005. He serves in an Advisory role to the SoccerPlus Education Center. He serves as a Trustee of several non-profit organizations such as the Connecticut Center for Science & Exploration and the Connecticut Children's Medical Center. He serves as a Comparator of the Eastern Connecticut Health Network Inc. ("ECHN"). He has funded, led and advised companies primarily focused on disruptive technologies. He is a recognized banking industry leader, technologist, entrepreneur, thought leader and frequent speaker. He has several articles published by leading journals and speaks regularly on the topics of technology, economics, strategic planning and globalization. He was awarded the Hartford Business Journal Business Person of the Year in 2005 and has been named one of the Hartford Business Journal's top executives under 40 and was an Ernst & Young New England Entrepreneur of the Year finalist. He was also one of the financial service industry's five most innovative leaders in 2005 according to Bank Technology News, a national financial services publication. He founded A Little Hope Foundation, which advocates for childrenâ€™s healthcare, education and emotional health. He is the Author of two books, Saving the American Dream—Main Street’s Last Stand and Too Small to Fail, numerous articles and has received many professional distinctions for his expertise in business and technology. Mr. Hernandez is a Certified Public Accountant. Mr. Hernandez holds a BS in Business Administration & Accounting and an MBA in Business Administration, both from San Diego State University.Read Full Background




Corporate Headquarters
75 Network DriveBurlington, Massachusetts 01803United StatesPhone: 978-640-6789Fax: --
Board Members Memberships
